{"cell_type":"code","exec_count":24,"id":"6f9ad2","input":"#Purpose of Cell Block: I will need a single identifier for each monitor, meaning I need to combine the identifier variables. The variables need to match the format shown in the markdown cell block above, meaning I will first need to add leading zeros to the data if needed. I only care about monitor locations (not individual monitor operations) so I need to drop all supplemental monitors at a site (e.g., see POCs)\n\nDF_aqs2019_loc2 <- DF_aqs2019_loc %>%\n    mutate('State_Code_Fix' = str_pad(State_Code, width = 2, pad = 0)) %>% #pad leading zero so state code always 2 char\n    mutate('County_Code_Fix' = str_pad(County_Code, width = 3, pad = 0)) %>% #pad leading zero so county code always 3 char\n    mutate('Site_Num_Fix' = str_pad(Site_Code, width = 4, pad = 0)) %>% #pad leading zero so site num always 4 char\n    mutate('POC_Fix' = str_pad(POC, width = 2, pad = 0)) %>% #pad leading zero so POC num always 2 char\n    select(-('State_Code':'Site_Code')) %>%  #drop old codes\n    unite(\n        col = 'AQS_Site_ID','State_Code_Fix', \n        'County_Code_Fix', \n        'Site_Num_Fix',\n        sep = \"\", \n        remove = TRUE\n    )\n\nprint(paste0(n_distinct(DF_aqs2019_loc2), \" rows before POC reduction\"))\n\nDF_aqs2019_loc3 <- DF_aqs2019_loc2 %>% #Drop latter POC's given I'm only concerned with location\n    group_by(AQS_Site_ID) %>%\n    filter(POC_Fix == min(POC_Fix)) %>%\n    ungroup() %>%\n    select(-('POC_Fix'))\n\nDF_aqs2019_loc4 <- DF_aqs2019_loc3 %>% #Correct bug where not all POC's were dropped\n  arrange(AQS_Site_ID, Date) %>%\n  group_by(AQS_Site_ID, Date) %>%\n  slice(1) %>%\n  ungroup()\n\nprint(paste0(n_distinct(DF_aqs2019_loc4), \" rows after POC reduction\"))\n\nhead(DF_aqs2019_loc4)\nprint(paste0(n_distinct(DF_aqs2019_loc4$AQS_Site_ID), \" PM2.5 monitors operating in 2019\"))\n\n#QA check to make sure Site ID len = 9\nDF_LenCheck <- DF_aqs2019_loc4 %>%\n    mutate(LenCheck = nchar(AQS_Site_ID)) %>% #add column to count the number of characters in AQS_Site_ID\n    filter(!LenCheck %in% c(9)) #filter to only show rows with different than 9 characters\n    \nhead(DF_LenCheck)\n#Conclusion: No AQS_Site_ID values contain more or less than 9 characters and extra instruments at a site appear to have been dropped (will confirm one POC later)","kernel":"ir","last":14452,"output":{"0":{"name":"stdout","text":"[1] \"638486 rows before POC reduction\"\n"},"1":{"name":"stdout","text":"[1] \"210090 rows after POC reduction\"\n"},"2":{"data":{"iframe":"4da1a1e2ccf3c749d5a1ed754e0c002c9ead318d","text/latex":"A tibble: 6 × 10\n\\begin{tabular}{llllllllll}\n POC & Latitude & Longitude & Address & State & County & City & Date & PM25\\_ugm3 & AQS\\_Site\\_ID\\\\\n <int> & <dbl> & <dbl> & <chr> & <chr> & <chr> & <chr> & <date> & <dbl> & <chr>\\\\\n\\hline\n\t 1 & 30.49748 & -87.88026 & FAIRHOPE HIGH SCHOOL, 1 PIRATE DRIVE, FAIRHOPE,  ALABAMA & Alabama & Baldwin & Fairhope & 2019-01-03 & 4.3 & 010030010\\\\\n\t 1 & 30.49748 & -87.88026 & FAIRHOPE HIGH SCHOOL, 1 PIRATE DRIVE, FAIRHOPE,  ALABAMA & Alabama & Baldwin & Fairhope & 2019-01-06 & 8.5 & 010030010\\\\\n\t 1 & 30.49748 & -87.88026 & FAIRHOPE HIGH SCHOOL, 1 PIRATE DRIVE, FAIRHOPE,  ALABAMA & Alabama & Baldwin & Fairhope & 2019-01-09 & 3.3 & 010030010\\\\\n\t 1 & 30.49748 & -87.88026 & FAIRHOPE HIGH SCHOOL, 1 PIRATE DRIVE, FAIRHOPE,  ALABAMA & Alabama & Baldwin & Fairhope & 2019-01-12 & 8.6 & 010030010\\\\\n\t 1 & 30.49748 & -87.88026 & FAIRHOPE HIGH SCHOOL, 1 PIRATE DRIVE, FAIRHOPE,  ALABAMA & Alabama & Baldwin & Fairhope & 2019-01-15 & 9.0 & 010030010\\\\\n\t 1 & 30.49748 & -87.88026 & FAIRHOPE HIGH SCHOOL, 1 PIRATE DRIVE, FAIRHOPE,  ALABAMA & Alabama & Baldwin & Fairhope & 2019-01-24 & 3.7 & 010030010\\\\\n\\end{tabular}\n","text/markdown":"\nA tibble: 6 × 10\n\n| POC &lt;int&gt; | Latitude &lt;dbl&gt; | Longitude &lt;dbl&gt; | Address &lt;chr&gt; | State &lt;chr&gt; | County &lt;chr&gt; | City &lt;chr&gt; 