{"cell_type":"code","exec_count":28,"id":"cc080a","input":"#Purpose of Cell Block: Establish Daily row for each monitor operating in 2019\nDF_aqs2019_loc5 <- monitor_date_grid %>%\n  left_join(\n    DF_aqs2019_loc4 %>%\n      select(AQS_Site_ID, Date, PM25_ugm3),\n    by = c(\"AQS_Site_ID\", \"Date\")\n  ) %>%\n  arrange(AQS_Site_ID, Date)\n\nhead(DF_aqs2019_loc5)\nprint(paste0(n_distinct(DF_aqs2019_loc5$AQS_Site_ID), \" PM2.5 monitors operating in 2019\"))\n\n#confirm that each monitor has 365 rows (i.e., extra POC were dropped so I can focus on monitor locations)\nmonitor_day_counts <- DF_aqs2019_loc5 %>%\n  group_by(AQS_Site_ID) %>%\n  summarise(\n    total_days = n(),\n    operating_days = sum(!is.na(PM25_ugm3)),\n    .groups = \"drop\"\n  ) %>%\n  arrange(total_days)\n\nhead(monitor_day_counts)\ntail(monitor_day_counts)\n\n\nn_rows <- n_distinct(DF_aqs2019_loc5)\n\nn_days2_QA <- n_rows / n_distinct(DF_aqs2019_loc5$AQS_Site_ID)\nprint(paste0(n_days2_QA, \" days per PM2.5 monitors operating in 2019\"))\n\n#Check total monitors operating on each date\nDaily_Monitors2019 <- DF_aqs2019_loc5 %>%\n    group_by(Date) %>%\n    summarise(daily_total_sites = n_distinct(AQS_Site_ID))\n\nprint(paste0(Daily_Monitors2019$daily_total_sites, \" PM2.5 monitors rows available on \", Daily_Monitors2019$Date))\n\n#Preserve output in processed data folder\nwrite_csv(DF_aqs2019_loc5, \"D_processed_data/air_monitors/daily_88101_2019_processed_v01.csv\")\nprint(\"Successfully exported dataset!\")\n\n#Conclusion: 996 PM2.5 monitors operated in the United States and its territories in 2019. Exported a dataset with 365 days for each of those monitors.","kernel":"ir","last":539,"output":{"0":{"data":{"iframe":"87ba62432976b6c4050a956a0fe149a1849c6c5a","text/latex":"A tibble: 6 × 9\n\\begin{tabular}{lllllllll}\n AQS\\_Site\\_ID & Latitude & Longitude & Address & State & County & City & Date & PM25\\_ugm3\\\\\n <chr> & <dbl> & <dbl> & <chr> & <chr> & <chr> & <chr> & <date> & <dbl>\\\\\n\\hli